HEADWORD: Cancriform
<hw>Can"cri*form</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Cancer</ets> + <ets>-form</ets>; cf. F.
<ets>cancriforme</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having the form of, or
resembling, a crab; crab-shaped.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Like a cancer; cancerous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cancrine</ent>⟦br⟧
